	   <a name=102347578957686></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102347578957686><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=102347578957686>Druid Lover!</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=102347578957686#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=122873><span id=Guru>Phreda the Hand</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>208 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Jun 7th 3:01 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>For a refreshing change of pace....<br><br>I like and respect Druids.&nbsp;&nbsp;My sister and I almost never bug druids for ports or SOW.  In the last year, I asked for a SOW once for a tough corpse retrieval. I offered 20 pp for it in desperation; the druid who answered not only gave me the SOW for free, but buffed me too, and ran with me to get my corpse.<br><br>Never shy about traveling, I have run the entire length of Faydwer or Antonica countless times without SOW.  Call me stupid if you like.... I appreciate that druids have better things to do than alleviate every other player a few extra moments of inconvenience.  I'd rather waddle on my merry way instead of spending several minutes begging, demanding, or shouting &quot;Can I get a SOW/port!&quot;<br><br>Cheers, ladies and gents.<br>&nbsp;<br>Phreda Biggles, 46 Warrior <br>Inebriator for the Order of the Keg <br><a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/journal.html?user=122873 target=_new>Tales of a Halfling Tank Girl</a></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
