	   <tr><td colspan=2>It's great to see a post from someone who doesn't mind running a zone! ::cheers:: I would like to point out that I really don't have any problems with sowing anyone. It doesn't take much mana and only a second to cast. A port means I need to leave the zone and sometimes that is just too much trouble as I'm either grouped or trying to accomplish something. But a sow is no trouble. At my level, I rarely have sow memmed as I use either Spirit of Eagle or wolf form, but memming a quick sow isn't that big a deal. So, if you need a sow, don't be worried about bugging a druid for one. Asking for a bunch of buffs is not appreciated on top of it though. If I have time, I just buff the person while I'm at it. If not, just the sow. I think you'll find druids don't mind giving sows.&nbsp;&nbsp;Also, as an FYI, Shammy's and higher level Rangers can sow too, so there is usually at least one person in a zone happy to sow you if you come to them.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
