	   <tr><td colspan=2>Just yesterday I took my 41 ranger to the dragon bridge in Eastern Wastes.&nbsp;&nbsp;This is the bridge that zones into Iceclad Ocean.  You can get there either from Iceclad or GD.  And if you are not familiar with the area I would highly recommend printing out maps from EQAtlas.  But since you are 38th level, I assume you’re already made use of that resource.  This is a great zone for both rangers and druids because of the large number of animals that wonder here. And at 41 almost all of them were dark blue, with a few light blues tossed in.<br><br>There are giants and Ry’Gorr orcs in this zone as well, but they do not wonder by the bridge.  The only non-animals that you should have to worry about are Snow Dervishes, which will wonder across the base of the bridge.  The animals here tend to be tougher than their namesakes elsewhere. Snow Cougars, for example, are dark blue here at 41 when they went light blue to me at 38 in Iceclad.  So always con before casting.  I had good luck pulling to the right of the bridge when facing out into the zone.  There is a Ry’Gorr outpost a short distance away, but I’ve not seen any of the orcs wonder to the bridge. And the pathing here tends to keep the animals running back and fourth instead of wondering deeper into the zone, at least when they’re getting beaten on.  <br><br>If you keep SoW up, you should be fine. The zone line is high up on the bridge, but it still works as a safety net.  Just keep in mind that mobs, including Snow Dervishes and an occasional Snow Griffon, will wonder across the lower section of the bridge. So pull to the side or high up onto the bridge.  And, at least on Seventh Hammer, there are hardly ever any other players around.  If my ranger didn’t go oom so often keeping himself healed it would be nearly perfect. <br><br>Best of luck,<br><br>&nbsp;<br><b>Namir Shadowstalker</b><br>Wood Elf Ranger, 51st Season<br><b>Calabar Silverthorn</b><br>Wood Elf Druid, 51st Season<br><b>Pait Spiritwalker</b><br>Vah Shir Shaman, 50th Season<br><br><b>Seventh Hammer</b></td></tr>
