	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, May 30th 8:38 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.48]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Most druids stop fearkiting by your level or earlier simply because it is so slow and inefficient to do it, as well as that by the time you hit level 40, it will be Impossible to do.&nbsp;&nbsp;The mobs just hit so hard by that time, even taking more than just two or three hits can kill you.<br><br>If you think about it, you can damage the mob MUCH more right now by fearing it, and then simply dropping to the ground and medding while it runs away, and then standing up and using the mana you have gained to throw another dot at it, than by running behind it and tapping it with your stick.<br><br>If meleeing works for you, and you enjoy it, by all means do it.  But it is not efficient, and the day is coming when you will Have to give it up. It will do you very little good to have a maxed melee skill when you cannot use it.  40+ mobs hit for 100 hps a shot sometimes.  If that fear spell wears off, and he turns around and whacks you and stuns you, or you get a couple of resists or an add, or you get a lag spike, you are quickly doing a CR.<br><br>If you want to melee and have some spell powers too, bards are more what you are looking for.  Druids Can melee up to level 60, I guess.  But they Cannot take the hits the mobs dish out at high levels. <br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
