	   <tr><td colspan=2>This may not be of much help, but I haven’t read anything about this weapon on the board so I thought I’d at least mention it.&nbsp;&nbsp;I met a very nice lady in Rivervale by the name of Kinsey, who gave my 20th season druid a great weapon.  It’s called the Staff of Living Sand:  <br><br>Damage: 24<br>Delay: 42 <br>Ratio: 1.75 Amazing<br>AC: +4 Sta: +4 Wis: +4 Mana: +40<br>Weight: 1.0<br>Effect: Smothering Sands<br><br>I often hit in the low forties and the proc, which starts taking effect at level 22, is extremely helpful.  Smothering Sands does 25 points of direct damage and a 144 hp DOT over 12 ticks.  <br><br>For me, this is an amazing weapon.  My main style of combat is fear kiting.  I snare an animal, DOT it, fear it and then beat on its butt with my stick.  This helps keep my weapon skill up, my attack skill up and when it turns and hits me a couple of times while I’m fearing it again my defense skill goes up.  I’m 28th level and this method has served me very well.<br><br>The only disadvantage is, of course, that I can only hold one item.  I plan to do quests to get good wisdom items to hold in both hands for when I’m in a group.  But for soloing, the high damage and extra DOT have proven invaluable.  <br><br>Allakhazam lists the value of the staff at 1,750pp.  But I’ve never watched the actions for it, so I don’t know how accurate that is.  <br><br>&nbsp;<br><b>Namir Shadowstalker</b><br>Wood Elf Ranger, 51st Season<br><b>Calabar Silverthorn</b><br>Wood Elf Druid, 51st Season<br><b>Pait Spiritwalker</b><br>Vah Shir Shaman, 50th Season<br><br><b>Seventh Hammer</b></td></tr>
