	   <tr><td colspan=2>&nbsp;&nbsp;If i were u i would hunt in nro at one of the derv camps at lvl 9 and then in the following few lvls head south to oasis.  Another option for lvl 9 would be to hunt at the chessboard in bb which is soso xp.The dervs are fairly good xp for your lvl and you will commonly get bronze gear to sell.  I would stay in oasis untill lvl 18 and then head to LOIO.  <br><br>  ALWAYS keep your skill lvls up... as kelanthor said.... or you will have a hard time fighting.  At your lvl i started tailoring and got my skill up pretty high and now i make quite a bit of cash off of it, and some of it i can use myself.<br><br>  Also keep improoving your gear.  For your chest try to get something like a foremans tunic and put a small wisdom deity in the range slot.  When you get to lvl 16 or so i would try to tackle the testament of vanear quest (+10mana +10wis).<br><br>Hope this helps......<br><br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Gileril Wolfang<br>Druid of the 52nd season<br>Tarew Marr Server<br>Member of Mithril Storm</td></tr>
